  hotspots:
  - title: The Rohen Fish Statue
    body: "This fish statue is a great introduction to one of Rohoen\u2019s main
      themes: water, movement, and quiet observation. Throughout the Japanese Friendship
      Garden, water appears in streams, the main pond, and the waterfall, helping
      create a calm atmosphere that encourages visitors to slow down and notice details.
      It also connects nicely to the garden\u2019s koi, which in Japanese culture
      are often associated with love, friendship, perseverance, and ambition."
    yaw: 0
    pitch: 0
